    * Js in Head or Body (Internal Js)
        * Html page can have any number of scripts in it, scripts can be place in head or boddy or both all are correct only

        * Inside style at ending part script

        * inside body ending part script

        * Placing scripts at the bottom of the <body> element improves the display speed, because script interpretation slows down the display.
            * because, browsers parse the html sequential from top to bottom when encounters script it will wait for some time or pauses html parsing and
              execute the script fully before moving on the next html elemnts

        * writing js on head or body is considered to be the internal js

    * External Js
        * the scripts can only place on that external js file only - external scrpyt.js file will have the script functions

        * External scripts are practical when same code is used in many webpages

        * ends with .js extension and to use external js put put name of the script file in the src atteribut inside the <Script> tag
            * like <Script src = "myScript.js"></Script>

            * the external js file should not have the script tag       -> Look At Workout - 6th Folder - 1st Basic Folder

        * External JavaScript Advantages
            * In external js there is some advantages:
                * It seperates html and code
                * It makes Html and Js code easier to read and maintain
                * Cached JavaScript files can speed up page loads

            * To add several script files to one page  - use several script tags:
                * Expample: <script src="myScript1.js"></script>
                            <script src="myScript2.js"></script>

